<blockquote><p><em>HunkyBill Shopify Expert experts.shopify.com/resistor-software Posts: 3590 Last edited 3 months ago</em><br />
Since a customer registration is just a form POST to Shopify, it is pretty simple to just disable this POST action. A Spam Bot will thus be unable to submit the form.<br />
When a real customer fills in the form, you can tell they are a real customer by asking them to do a simple test. For example, if they are really human, ask them a question like what is 5+8 in a text box. If they answer 13, you pretty much know it is not a Bot.<sup><a href="#footnote_15_70580" id="identifier_15_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="How many humans (by smell, as he says) would fail this test, in your estimation ?
Because that's the beauty of it : more bots pass it than humans fail it.">xvi</a></sup> Or use a Captcha. Whatever. If they pass the human smell test, submit the form to Shopify.<br />
Problem solved. Why the angst? This type of form process has been around pretty much as long as Bots... nothing new here.<sup><a href="#footnote_16_70580" id="identifier_16_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="`Why are you angry at the world not working -- it never worked! Progress!!!`
He has a point, actually. The imperial ecosystem deals with Cary's problems through sulfozinum injections, he'd better watch out.">xvii</a></sup><br />
Custom Shopify Apps built just for you! hunkybill@gmail.com</p></blockquote>
<blockquote><p><em>Coel May Member Posts:15 Last edited 3 months ago</em><br />
For those more curious, the script I used can be found at stackoverflow.com/questions/1217824/post-to-another-page-within-a-php-script<br />
All one needs to do is set the url [e.g. http://<yourshopurlhere>/account], and set the $fields array so it contains the values from the sign-up page:</p>
<p>"form_type" => "create_customer",<br />
"utf8" => "✓"<sup><a href="#footnote_17_70580" id="identifier_17_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="This cutsy idiocy is being used everywhere. Meh.">xviii</a></sup>,<br />
"customer[first_name]" => "Secret",<br />
"customer[last_name]" => "Squirrel",<br />
"customer[email]" => "dodgyemailaccounthere@live.com",<br />
"customer[password]" => "dodgyemailaccounthere"</p>
<p>Then run the script and hey presto! A new customer account has just been created on your store.<br />
There is apparently no referrer checking<sup><a href="#footnote_18_70580" id="identifier_18_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="`Referrer` checking being their naive guess at what a Republic'd look like. Some way to go to the WoT, and most steps on it they very pointedly do not wish to take.">xix</a></sup> done anywhere in the account creation, and as far as I can tell, this is something only Shopify can do something about as it is not part of a :"theme".<br />
DISCLALIMER: I post this information for education/awareness purposes only.<sup><a href="#footnote_19_70580" id="identifier_19_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Because intent matters. He believes this. He actually believes this.">xx</a></sup></p></blockquote>
