<p>But no - you can't "stop them register". Ask.fm is using Google's latest captcha thing (that thing where you have to click on pizza or whatever, shop awnings), and it isn't helping them.  [<a href="#identifier_14_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_15_70580" class="footnote">How many humans (by smell, as he says) would fail this test, in your estimation ?</p>
<p>Because that's the beauty of it : more bots pass it than humans fail it. [<a href="#identifier_15_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_16_70580" class="footnote">"Why are you angry at the world not working -- it never worked! Progress!!!"</p>
<p>He has a point, actually. The imperial ecosystem deals with Cary's problems through sulfozinum injections, he'd better watch out. [<a href="#identifier_16_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_17_70580" class="footnote">This cutsy idiocy is being used everywhere. Meh. [<a href="#identifier_17_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_18_70580" class="footnote">"Referrer" checking being their naive guess at what a Republic'd look like. Some way to go to the WoT, and most steps on it they very pointedly do not wish to take. [<a href="#identifier_18_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_19_70580" class="footnote">Because intent matters. He believes this. He actually believes this. [<a href="#identifier_19_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_20_70580" class="footnote">Imagine that, they printed a number on the form. These dorks count for literate, they're citizens, they get to vote, serve on juries, they're preparing your food and educating your children.</p>
<p>And they try out with some regularity the magical power of amulets. Hey -- Ivy League degree makes your life better and so on, right ? Why shouldn't the string "8+3=?" printed prominently on a form protect one from bots much like the "This Property Secured By SecuProp" protects their house from breaking&#038;entering ? What do you mean it doesn't ?!?! Well sometimes it doesn't but it does when it does, which really means when it doesn't not protect it... [<a href="#identifier_20_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_21_70580" class="footnote">Gota xsell that app! [<a href="#identifier_21_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_22_70580" class="footnote">In a word -- yes. It's great for "the economy", and good enough for you. In fact, it's the only thread "the economy" is hanging on by. Do you want a 401k like your daddy had or don't you ? [<a href="#identifier_22_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_23_70580" class="footnote">Right.</p>
<p>And if they fixed it, how'd they sell you an app ? [<a href="#identifier_23_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_24_70580" class="footnote">You know ? [<a href="#identifier_24_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_25_70580" class="footnote">As the great Eric the Clown once said, "This is just a gig, it's not my life. I don't know who Bozo is - what!"  [<a href="#identifier_25_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_26_70580" class="footnote">I guess I win that bet -- not paid. [<a href="#identifier_26_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_27_70580" class="footnote">But they <em>will</em>! For to progress!</p>
<p>I bet they'll even support Python 3! [<a href="#identifier_27_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_28_70580" class="footnote">You see ? He added "required" to the answer box! This does something - because unlike the previous 5+3 displayed amulet, this one is the more potent variety, stuck in the very guts of the strange Internet beast.</p>
<p>And, glory of glories - it <em>seems</em> to have worked. Because it always does. [<a href="#identifier_28_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_29_70580" class="footnote">Taleb explains why. [<a href="#identifier_29_70580" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li></ol>
              <div>
